article.headline: E. Michigan 65, Bowling Green 63
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Jesse Bunkley scored 17 points and made a three-point play that put Eastern Michigan ahead to stay with 28 seconds remaining Saturday, setting up a 65-63 victory over Bowling Green. Eastern Michigan (9-15, 4-7 Mid-American) wasted a 12-point lead in the second half before pulling it out. Jarred Axon also had 17 points and went 10-of-10 on free throws. Martin Samarco scored 21 points for Bowling Green (11-13, 2-9) and led the second-half comeback, but missed a 3-pointer at the buzzer. Axon's jumper put Eastern Michigan ahead 48-36 with 12:33 to play, matching the Eagles' biggest lead of the game. Bowling Green then went on an 18-5 run that featured a jumper and six free throws by Samarco. Ryne Hamblet had a 3-pointer and a jumper during the run, which put Bowling Green ahead 54-53 with 6:15 left. There were three ties before Bunkley's three-point play -- he was fouled by Hamblet while making a layup -- put Eastern ahead to stay 64-61 with 28 seconds left. Hamblet's two free throws cut it to 64-63 with 22 seconds left. Brandon Bowdry made the second of his two free throws with 16 seconds left, and Samarco missed his 3-pointer at the buzzer.
